quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  39,48,"And the evils they earned appeared to them, and the thing they used to mock at descended upon them."
  39,49,"So when some hardship reaches man, he prays to Us; then later when We bestow a favour upon him, he says, “I obtained this only because of some knowledge”; in fact it is a test, but most of them do not have any knowledge."
  39,50,"Those before them also said the same, so their earnings did not benefit them at all."
  39,51,"Therefore the evils of their earnings befell them; and those who are unjust among them – soon the evils of the earnings will befall them, and they cannot escape."
  39,52,"Do they not know that Allah eases the sustenance for whomever He wills, and restricts it? Indeed in this are signs for the People who Believe."
  39,53,"Proclaim (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him), “O my* slaves, who have wronged themselves, do not lose hope in Allah’s mercy; indeed Allah forgives all sins; indeed He only is the Oft Forgiving, the Most Merciful.” (All Muslims are truly the slaves of Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him.)"
  39,54,"“And incline towards your Lord and submit to Him, before the punishment comes you and then you may not be helped.”"
  39,55,"“And follow this, the best among all, which has been sent down towards you from your Lord, before the punishment comes suddenly upon you whilst you are unaware.”"
  39,56,"So that no soul may say, “Alas! The failures that I committed regarding Allah – and indeed I used to mock!”"
